replies.body:
There is a bit of untapped creativity in mage builds that you can use against assassins.

1. If you really have trouble with a specific type of opponent, make a rune page that swaps in extra flat armor.
{{item:1029}} 

2. Consider bringing barrier over ignite and try to farm and scale into team fights.
{{summoner:14}} > {{summoner:21}} 

3. Stop finishing your mana item before building Zhonyas. In converse, stop rushing Zhonyas before buying mana. If you were going to build morelonomicion build the Idol first and then rush the Zhonyas.
{{item:3114}}+{{item:1001}} > {{item:3191}} > {{item:3157}} > {{item:3165}} 

4. Consider Archangel staff or Rod of Ages over your usual mana item for matchups against assassins. Both make you much harder to kill, with stacked Archangel acting as a second Zhonyas and ROA making you much tankier to assassins. Tear of the Goddess and Catalyst will provide good mana regen in lane in the mean time.
{{item:3040}} {{item:3027}}
